================================================================================
                         NOTETAKER AI - QUICK START                         
================================================================================

‚ö° ONE-COMMAND STARTUP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

METHOD 1: From Terminal
   $ make start

   This will:
   ‚úì Start Ollama (if not running)
   ‚úì Check/install LLM model
   ‚úì Start backend server
   ‚úì Open browser to http://localhost:8000/upload


METHOD 2: Desktop Shortcuts (Recommended!)
   START:  Double-click "start-notetaker.command"
   STOP:   Double-click "stop-notetaker.command"
   
   Both are on your Desktop - drag to Dock for quick access!


METHOD 3: Manual
   Terminal 1: $ ollama serve
   Terminal 2: $ make dev
   Browser:    http://localhost:8000/upload


üõë STOPPING EVERYTHING (Save RAM!)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Desktop:   Double-click "stop-notetaker.command"
   Terminal:  $ make stop
   Alias:     $ notes-stop

   Kills both Ollama and backend. Frees up ~500MB RAM!


üîÑ RESTARTING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   $ make restart

   Stops everything and starts fresh.


üìç MAIN URLS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Upload Notes:    http://localhost:8000/upload
   Search Notes:    http://localhost:8000/search  
   Manage Files:    http://localhost:8000/manager
   Theme Editor:    http://localhost:8000/theme-editor


üîß USEFUL COMMANDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   make start           Start everything
   make stop            Stop all services (kills Ollama + Backend)
   make restart         Restart everything
   make ps              Check what's running
   make clean           Nuclear option - kill EVERYTHING
   make check-ollama    Check if Ollama is working
   make fix-ollama      Install LLM model
   make db-health       Check database status
   make db-cleanup      Clean orphaned vectors
   make test            Run quick test


üí° FIRST TIME SETUP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Install Ollama:    brew install ollama
2. Install model:     make fix-ollama
3. Start app:         make start


üêõ TROUBLESHOOTING
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Problem: Port 8000 already in use
   Solution: make stop

Problem: Ollama not running
   Solution: make check-ollama

Problem: No LLM model
   Solution: make fix-ollama

Problem: PDF not formatted nicely
   Solution: Check http://localhost:8000/api/health/ollama


üìä WORKFLOW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Start:  Double-click "start-notetaker.command" (or: make start)
2. Upload: Go to /upload, select class, upload notes
3. PDFs:   Auto-generated with AI formatting
4. Search: Go to /search, ask questions about your notes
5. Stop:   Double-click "stop-notetaker.command" (or: make stop)


üéØ DAILY USE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Morning:
   Double-click "start-notetaker.command"    # Opens browser automatically

During Day:
   - Upload notes as you take them
   - PDFs saved in latex/output/
   - Search when studying

Evening:
   Double-click "stop-notetaker.command"     # Saves RAM (~500MB freed!)

üí° Tip: Drag both .command files to your Dock for one-click access!


================================================================================
                            Happy Note Taking! üìö                            
